chunk_content: H E A New health worker graduates of pre-service training institution or program will be counted as PEPFAR L supported when PEPFAR is supporting the training of new health worker graduates, including: T • Tuition and fees - At least 50% of the students' tuition and fees were or will be provided by H PEPFAR for at least 6 months of their education. S Y • Curriculum development – The students received or will receive training where PEPFAR S curriculum development was essential to qualify them for their trained role. T • Infrastructure - The students received or will receive 6 months or more of education at an E M institution that could not have supported their education without PEPFAR-supported S infrastructure improvements (classrooms, dormitories, utilities).
